{
  "uuid": "911a5e6fdee72ab53467084152bab68a",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accountant (In-House Bookkeeping)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Role Summary</strong></u></p><p>We are looking for a detail-oriented Accountant with 2–3 years of experience to manage in-house bookkeeping and accounting records. This role requires someone who is systems-savvy, methodical, and capable of maintaining accurate accounts independently, while leading a small team, coordinating with management and external accountants when required.</p><p>This is not a purely reporting role. You will be hands-on with day-to-day entries, reconciliations, and documentation.</p><p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u><br /><strong>Bookkeeping & Accounting</strong></p><ul><li>Maintain full set of accounts for assigned companies</li><li>Perform daily / weekly bookkeeping:<br />- AP & AR entries<br />- Bank and cash reconciliations<br />- Journal entries and adjustments</li><li>Ensure invoices, receipts, and vouchers are properly recorded and filed (e-filing)</li><li>Track intercompany transactions and reconciliations</li><li>Support month-end closing and management accounts preparation</li></ul><p><strong>Systems & Process </strong></p><ul><li>Well versed with accounting systems (e.g. Odoo, Xero, QuickBooks, SAP, or similar ERP systems)</li><li>Ensure data accuracy and consistency across systems </li><li>Assist in improving accounting workflows and internal controls </li><li>Coordinate with external accountants / auditors for year-end and statutory matters</li></ul><p><strong></strong><br /><strong>Compliance & Support</strong></p><ul><li>Support GST reporting and documentation (training can be provided if needed) </li><li>Ensure proper documentation for audits and third-party reviews </li><li>Assist with ad-hoc accounting and finance-related tasks</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements </strong></u><br /><strong>Experience & Skills</strong></p><p><p><ul><li>2–3 years of relevant accounting / bookkeeping experience </li><li>Prior experience in in-house accounting preferred</li><li>Comfortable handling hands-on bookkeeping (not just review work)</li><li>Well-versed in accounting software / ERP systems</li><li>Strong Excel skills (VLOOKUP/XLOOKUP, pivot tables, basic formulas)</li></ul></p></p><p><strong>Traits We Value</strong></p><p><p><ul><li>Detail-oriented and organised</li><li>Systematic, disciplined, and process-driven</li><li>Able to work independently and meet deadlines</li><li>Practical mindset — focuses on getting things done correctly</li><li>Comfortable leading teams</li></ul></p></p><p><u><strong>Qualifications</strong></u></p><p><p><ul><li>Diploma / Degree in Accounting, Finance, or related field</li><li>Professional certification (ACCA / ISCA / CPA) is a plus but not mandatory</li></ul></p></p><p><u><strong>What We Offer</strong></u></p><ul><li>Stable in-house executive role with real ownership of the accounts</li><li>Exposure to multi-company and multi-currency accounting</li><li>Opportunity to work closely with management</li><li>Structured systems and processes (with room for improvement)</li><li>Competitive salary commensurate with experience</li></ul>",
